25:34.612 --> 25:37.440
You want me to take care of you?

25:37.923 --> 25:39.416
I didn't even think you liked me.

25:39.460 --> 25:41.055
I like you.

25:41.660 --> 25:44.476
I just don't like some of
the choices you've made.

25:44.516 --> 25:46.661
You don't like any of
the choices I've made.

25:46.724 --> 25:47.675
Oh.

25:50.322 --> 25:53.375
Why do you always choose
men who cheat on you?

25:53.406 --> 25:54.706
I've got news for you, mom.

25:54.740 --> 25:56.860
George never cheated
on me. I cheated on him.

25:56.872 --> 25:57.755
And he left me,

25:57.792 --> 25:59.657
letting people think that
it was the other way around.

25:59.678 --> 26:01.096
- What?
- And wait...

26:01.089 --> 26:01.952
Men?

26:02.303 --> 26:04.643
Marshall was the only other man in my life.

26:05.463 --> 26:07.321
Except for Jeff. But never mind.

26:07.346 --> 26:08.847
Yeah, Marshall.

26:09.166 --> 26:10.669
He cheated on you too.

26:10.789 --> 26:12.276
What do you know about that?

26:14.859 --> 26:17.168
I didn't not go to the funeral

26:17.168 --> 26:19.695
because it was at your church and not mine,

26:19.898 --> 26:22.967
I just didn't want to go
to that scoundrel's funeral,

26:23.001 --> 26:25.707
especially when he died going back to

26:25.751 --> 26:27.415
see his girlfriend.

26:28.229 --> 26:30.193
Did you know he had a girlfriend?

26:30.313 --> 26:31.376
I found out.

26:32.183 --> 26:33.260
How did you find out?

26:33.253 --> 26:34.993
Like missionaries don't gossip?

26:35.113 --> 26:36.212
He had a child.

26:37.516 --> 26:38.716
His name is Jacob.

26:38.751 --> 26:40.792
He found me last year and

26:41.030 --> 26:42.268
he came here

26:42.688 --> 26:45.053
and he met Grace and tom and

26:45.724 --> 26:46.791
then he went home.

26:47.726 --> 26:49.345
You deserve better.

26:52.765 --> 26:55.466
I think that's the nicest
thing you've ever said to me.

26:57.836 --> 26:58.803
Ever.

27:00.672 --> 27:02.874
And why are you saying this to me now?

27:02.908 --> 27:04.609
Because you want to move in here?

27:04.643 --> 27:05.710
I want to...

27:06.812 --> 27:08.479
get to know you.

27:10.373 --> 27:12.600
- And Grace. And Tom.
- Why now?

27:12.618 --> 27:14.014
Why not now?

27:14.070 --> 27:15.109
Because mom,

27:15.141 --> 27:18.219
I don't want my children to
be subjected to your judgment,

27:18.269 --> 27:19.690
the way I was.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.379
I'm sorry.

27:22.230 --> 27:24.989
I just don't know how not to judge people.

27:25.057 --> 27:26.509
It's a bad habit.

27:26.765 --> 27:29.415
I got it from going to church, our church,

27:29.535 --> 27:31.045
the church that I

27:31.165 --> 27:34.073
joined when I got married to your dad.

27:34.573 --> 27:35.950
I didn't realize.

27:36.441 --> 27:37.842
Yeah, well...

27:38.052 --> 27:40.091
I was into it for many years

27:40.135 --> 27:42.725
and then I got this stupid diagnosis.

27:43.615 --> 27:45.665
I wanted to see you

27:46.147 --> 27:48.024
and ask for forgiveness.

27:49.019 --> 27:50.464
And he said no.

27:50.502 --> 27:52.798
And I said I was going to do it anyway and,

27:52.918 --> 27:55.056
basically, I was shunned

27:55.176 --> 27:56.933
for not obeying my husband.

27:56.939 --> 27:58.654
After all these years.

27:58.697 --> 27:59.831
Shunned?

27:59.865 --> 28:01.106
Forty years

28:01.119 --> 28:04.349
and the one time I really wanted something,

28:04.397 --> 28:05.886
he refused me,

28:06.224 --> 28:07.706
and he divorced me,

28:07.739 --> 28:09.384
took another wife,

28:09.504 --> 28:12.086
someone who would obey him.

28:13.856 --> 28:16.584
I used to be a fun person,

28:16.766 --> 28:18.355
I liked to dance,

28:18.617 --> 28:20.601
I liked to have a good time,

28:20.820 --> 28:23.648
I was very popular in high school.

28:24.311 --> 28:26.532
I even planned to go to college,

28:26.652 --> 28:31.137
Europe, become a writer or an artist but...

28:32.698 --> 28:34.599
I met your father and...

28:37.244 --> 28:40.671
Do you really think Grace
should be getting married?

28:40.706 --> 28:41.772
(Sighs)

28:41.892 --> 28:42.840
Yeah.

28:45.070 --> 28:46.410
Hi.

28:46.845 --> 28:48.713
Oh. Hi, Grace.

28:48.747 --> 28:50.182
I just wanted to tell you,

28:50.302 --> 28:52.384
in case you haven't heard,

28:52.851 --> 28:54.305
Jack and I are getting married.

28:54.330 --> 28:56.150
I heard. Great news.

29:00.130 --> 29:02.145
- I'm going to Harvard.
- What!

29:02.145 --> 29:04.022
- Wow.
- That is so unfair.

29:04.041 --> 29:05.248
It's fair. I earned it.

29:05.248 --> 29:07.544
I made the grades, I went
to med camp every summer.

29:07.538 --> 29:09.378
- How is it not fair?
- Oh you're just trying to make me jealous.

29:09.434 --> 29:11.092
Jealous of what? Of my school?

29:11.117 --> 29:12.838
Yes. You didn't even want to go to Harvard.

29:12.831 --> 29:14.639
- Yeah, I did.
- Well, so did I!

29:14.658 --> 29:16.660
- Then you should have applied.
- I did. I didn't get in!

29:16.685 --> 29:20.051
I don't believe this. I'm
so much smarter than you.

29:20.064 --> 29:22.091
No, you're not, because I never
let relationships in high school

29:22.128 --> 29:24.268
interfere with my life plans.

29:27.264 --> 29:28.653
I would like to sleep with you.

29:29.454 --> 29:30.568
- What!
- Yeah.

29:30.589 --> 29:33.639
When we had sex before, it
was really great, wasn't it?

29:33.759 --> 29:35.526
- I guess.
- You guess!

29:35.560 --> 29:37.112
Okay. Yeah.

29:37.125 --> 29:38.226
We have so much in common,

29:38.257 --> 29:39.515
we want the same things out of life,

29:39.565 --> 29:44.057
we're both smart and ambitious
and we're both winners!

29:44.177 --> 29:47.199
You sound a little crazy. Are you okay?

29:47.205 --> 29:49.977
