33:59.170 --> 34:01.629
All right. Old beef.

34:04.275 --> 34:05.539
New meat.

34:05.821 --> 34:07.654
Boykewich beef.

34:08.686 --> 34:10.339
There is a difference!

34:12.152 --> 34:13.860
Hey, kiddo.

34:14.436 --> 34:16.181
This is Eli, the chef.
Eli, my daughter Amy.

34:16.237 --> 34:17.915
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

34:17.984 --> 34:19.315
- You too.
- You want anything to eat?

34:19.436 --> 34:20.286
Not really.

34:20.330 --> 34:23.308
Kind of lost my appetite when I
talked to Grace this afternoon.

34:24.215 --> 34:26.712
All right, we'll do this later. Thanks.

34:29.458 --> 34:31.655
Before you say anything,
I just want you to know

34:31.980 --> 34:33.400
that Kathleen and I are
going to get married,

34:33.456 --> 34:34.608
we almost got married last weekend.

34:34.627 --> 34:36.690
Dad, you know that I already knew that.

34:36.754 --> 34:38.210
Is it my fault if you
sent your husband down here

34:38.210 --> 34:39.806
to talk to me this morning
instead of coming yourself?

34:39.844 --> 34:42.141
Grace told me that, not Ricky,

34:42.647 --> 34:46.382
and I wanted you to know first about Ricky
and me before we told everyone at school.

34:46.413 --> 34:48.353
You didn't care enough to tell me first.

34:48.396 --> 34:50.110
